body.description: Cambria 2 XL Booster Seat combines space and room to grow, without compromising on safety or comfort. Suitable from 40 - 120 lb / 18 - 54 kg, expect 8 years of safety from just one booster seat. Awarded IIHS Best Bet Booster Seat, Cambria 2s extra wide design has plenty of room for your childs shoulders, hips, and legs. The ergonomic car seat base has been designed for complete child comfort and features 2x 2-in-1 fold-away cup holders and storage compartments to accommodate all your little one's cups, toys, and more on the move. Integrated LATCH connectors and front adjusters allow you to quickly tighten the booster car seat to the vehicle seat. The bright and bold covers allow your little one to arrive in style, with easy remove covers that can be machine washed and constructed from practical fabrics that can be wiped clean. When they are ready, the Cambria 2 transforms from a high-back booster to a backless booster seat offering two seats in one. So, whether youre taking them to school, on a playdate with a friend, or an overnight visit with grandparents, Cambria 2 will always provide a comfortable and safe journey.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 22, 2022
reviews.reviewText: We’re officially Diono fans. I’d heard about the brand but didn’t know anyone who owned a Diono product. So glad I gave them a try. For starters, the safety ratings were good, it’s very lightweight, the installation was super easy- normally I have my fiancé do the installation because car seats and I do not mesh well lol- I installed this, alone, in a snap. Adjusting the backrest for height is simple and requires almost no effort. Taking the back off, to make it a backless booster, can be accomplished in seconds. My 6yo daughter says it’s comfortable. She loves the colors and the cup holders. Also, the arm rests are actually a decent size. Some of the booster seats on the market have these ridiculous arm rest, too short and too narrow, not sure what those companies are thinking. These are wide enough for her to actually set her arm on and long enough too. I was concerned about it being too big for my Jeep. My backseats are pretty small/narrow and most car seats are too big for them, but with a little wiggling and tightening, it fits perfectly.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 15, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Big, but if you got the room so worth it
reviews.reviewText: I bought two of these booster seats because my daughter's 6 & 5 year olds were out growing their car seats. The modern sleek look of these seats had me stopping and reading the reviews and although some stated they were on the big side, I took a chance on them and I'm so glad I did. I have an older model Honda Odyssey and the seats fit perfectly. They were easy to assemble as you snap together the top and bottom part which were separated in the box. It was pretty simple to hook them in my van as I attached the two ancore hooks on the bottom of the booster seat to the van's seat. The seats are sturdy once strapped in correctly and don't move around. Then I weaved the seat belt through the hole in the booster chair as seen in pic. They feel nice, look nice, and have good safety features as the sides are wide enough for protection and comfort. They also have two pull out cup holders on both sides of the seats that can fit juice boxes and snacks. These seats are really nice as I've gotten complaments from other moms about them too, so if you have the room these booster seats are great to have.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewText: My daughter still sits in her Diono Radian 5 point harness seat in our main vehicle, but I wanted something in our secondary vehicle without spending another $$$ on a second big seat. This is perfect for quick trips, as she fits all the requirements to sit in this seat. The color is fantastic. The latch system makes it a breeze to install into the vehicle. The car seat belt positions perfectly when my child is buckled in. I love that both cup holders can be folded in when not in use. I wish this was around back when my older kids were in car seats. Definitely recommend this seat for children who are old enough/ big enough to sit in a booster seat.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars No more car fights with my 4 year old….
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. My daughter and I have been getting in car fights since she’s been in a literal backward facing car seat, absolutely hates getting buckled wishes she could just run free throughout the car. So when she finally was eligible for a booster seat, over 40 pounds, I knew I was going to get one she loved so we could eliminate at least half of the tantrums. Obviously, this is a little bit more expensive than the average booster seat but I was thinking of investment since it would be one that she was going to have for years to come. Plus I have an infant daughter who would use it after her. She chose this car seat based on its color, pink, her favorite. And I chose it based on Safety and easy installation. We love this booster. It has so much room for growth so I definitely think it will make it till she’s six or seven years old and it’s very durable. We’ve had it for over six months at this point and it still looks brand new, the two cupholders on the side can be pushed in or pulled out which I love so they don’t get all funky With old candy or old snacks. And it isn’t a complete eyesore in my car so 10 out of 10 recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I bought this for my 5-year-old, who weighs approx. 55 pounds and is almost 4 feet. This chair was great. Super light, colors are vibrant, and she says it super comfy. Very pleased.
Nice car seat, fits nice in my car (Volkswagon Passat). My 5 year old loves it, fits well and comfortably in it.

I viewed this booster seat on Walmart website & checked Amazon, Amazon was $10 less & faster shipping got it in 2 days purchased 2 for both of our vehicles, It’s absolutely beautiful, extremely bright colours my daughter was so excited, it’s super soft & comfortable, it installs like a breeze, my daughter finds the head rest amazing when she falls asleep her head doesn’t flop all over, Best purchase ever!!

Love this seat! Easy to set up, install (with latches) so seat doesn’t move around when child not in it, and son says it’s very comfortable. It feels sturdy compared to many booster seats and the price point is great! Would buy again!

I really love this booster seat, they fact that it is all black is amazing my son's car seat was grey and you could see every stain imaginable. The cup holders can be stowed away when not in use and you are able to remove the high back later on to make it a backless booster. The lower latch anchors give me a little piece of mind and probably also helps prevent any shaking as you drive without your child in the seat. It is super easy to install it took me maybe 2 minutes to put it in my car. Very happy with my purchase and would highly recommend this booster to anyone.
